A function is a group of reusable code which can be called anywhere in program
Functions allow a programmer to divide a big program into a number of small and manageable functions

functions like alert() and write()


Function Definition:
====================

The most common way to define a function in JavaScript is by using the function keyword, followed by a unique function name, 
a list of parameters (that might be empty), and a statement block surrounded by curly braces.

Syn:
=====

<script type="text/javascript">
   <!--
      function functionname(parameter-list)
      {
         statements
      }
   //-->
</script>


Example:
=========

<script type="text/javascript">
   <!--
      function sayHello()
      {
         alert("Hello Java Script");
      }
   //-->
  </script>
  
  Calling a Function:
  =================================
  
  
  <html>
   <head>
   
      <script type="text/javascript">
         function sayHello()
         {
            document.write ("Hello Java Script!");
         }
      </script>
      
   </head>
   <body>
      <p>Click the following button to call the function</p>
      
      <form>
         <input type="button" onclick="sayHello()" value="Say Hello">
      </form>
      
      <p>Use different text in write method and then try...</p>
   </body>
</html>

